1 b. Complete any additional class hours required for grade level IV.
2 (3b) For inspector certification, applicant shall satisfy the following conditions:
3 a. Complete the point-of-sale inspector education approved by the
4 Board.
5 b. Complete any additional class hours required for point-of-sale
6 inspector certification.
7 c. Hold current and satisfactory certification of grade level IV contractor,
8 or Authorized On-Site Wastewater Evaluator or subsurface operator
9 certification for a minimum of two years.
10 d. In lieu of the experience requirements in this subdivision, an applicant
11 may instead complete the approved education requirements for the
12 grade IV contractor certification as required by the Board. This
13 sub-subdivision shall not apply to a person certified as a grade II
14 contractor.
15 (3c) For Authorized On-Site Wastewater Evaluator, applicant shall complete the
16 Authorized On-Site Wastewater Evaluator education approved by the Board.
17 (3d) For Private Compliance Inspector, applicant shall satisfy the following
18 conditions:
19 a. Complete the Private Compliance Inspector education approved by the
20 Board.
21 b. Complete any additional class hours required by the Board for
22 compliance inspector certification.
23 c. Have a minimum of 5 years of experience as a certified contractor,
24 Authorized On-Site Wastewater Evaluator, subsurface operator, or a
25 registered environmental health specialist with experience in on-site
26 wastewater matters.
27 d. Not be employed by a local health department.
28 (4) Repealed by Session Laws 2010-31, s. 13.2(l), effective July 1, 2010.
29 (5) Completes any additional training program designed by the Board specific to
30 the grade level for which the applicant is applying.
31 (6) Pays the applicable fees set by the Board for the particular application.
32 (7) Passes a written or oral examination that tests the applicant's proficiency in all
33 of the following areas:
34 a. Principles of public and environmental health associated with on-site
35 wastewater systems.
36 b. Principles of construction and safety.
37 c. Technical and practical knowledge of on-site wastewater systems.
38 d. Laws and rules related to the installation, construction, repair,
39 point-of-sale inspection, evaluation, or private compliance inspection
40 of on-site wastewater systems.
41 (8) Holds sufficient general liability coverage and professional liability coverage
42 for the project as well as errors and omissions coverage, where applicable.
43 …."
44 SECTION 2.(b) G.S. 90A-78 reads as rewritten:
45 "§ 90A-78. Certification renewal.
46 (a) Renewal. – All certifications shall expire on December 31 of each year unless they
47 are renewed. To renew a certification, a contractor, inspector, Authorized On-Site Wastewater
48 Evaluator, or Private Compliance Inspector must meet all of the following conditions:
49 (1) Submit an application for renewal on the form prescribed by the Board, which
50 includes all supporting documents requested on the renewal form.form, and
