16 ON-SITE WASTEWATER SYSTEM CHANGES
17 SECTION 3.(a) G.S. 130A-335 reads as rewritten:
18 "§ 130A-335. Wastewater collection, treatment and disposal; rules.
19 …
20 (c) A wastewater system subject to approval under rules of the Commission shall be
21 reviewed and approved under rules of a local board of health in the following circumstances:
22 (1) The local board of health, on its own motion, has requested the Department to
23 review its proposed rules concerning wastewater systems; and
24 (2) The local board of health has adopted by reference the wastewater system
25 rules adopted by the Commission, with any more stringent modifications or
26 additions deemed necessary by the local board of health to protect the public
27 health. Local boards of health shall use historical experience to establish
28 modifications or additions to rules established by the Commission; andA local
29 board of health may not adopt any more stringent modifications or additions
30 unless the local board of health has entered into an agreement with the
31 Department pursuant to G.S. 143-300.8, and the Department has reviewed and
32 approved the modification or addition; and
33 (3) The Department has has, consistent with subsection (c3) of this section, found
34 that the rules, including modifications or additions to the Commission's rules,
35 of the local board of health concerning wastewater collection, treatment and
36 disposal systems are at least as stringent as rules adopted by the Commission
37 and are sufficient and necessary to safeguard the public health.
38 …
39 (c3) The Department shall adopt rules of evidence to determine the validity of proposals
40 from local boards of health seeking modifications or additions to rules established by the
41 Commission based solely on the necessity to protect the public health. In evaluating the validity
42 of a local health department's proposed modifications or additions pursuant to subdivision (3) of
43 subsection (c) of this section, the Department shall hold public hearings and notice those hearings
44 the Department's webpage upon application for modification or addition of Commission rules by
45 the local health department. The Department shall make its findings available to the public before
46 approving or denying a proposed modification or addition.
47 (d) The Department may, upon its own motion, upon the request of a local board of health
48 or upon the request of a citizen of an affected county, review its findings under subsection (c) of
49 this section.
50 The Department shall review its findings under subsection (c) of this section upon
51 modification by the Commission of the rules applicable to wastewater systems. The Department
