8 …
9 (f) The rules of the Commission and the rules of the local board of health shall classify
10 systems of wastewater collection, treatment and disposal according to size, type of treatment and
11 any other appropriate factors. The rules shall provide construction requirements, including
12 pretreatment and system control requirements, standards for operation, maintenance, monitoring,
13 reporting, and ownership requirements for each classification of systems of wastewater
14 collection, treatment and disposal in order to prevent, as far as reasonably possible, any
15 contamination of the land, groundwater and surface waters. The Department and local health
16 departments may impose conditions on the issuance of permits and may revoke the permits for
17 failure of the system to satisfy the conditions, the rules, or this Article. Permits other than
18 improvement permits shall be valid for a period prescribed by rule. Improvement permits shall
19 be valid upon a showing satisfactory to the Department or the local health department that the
20 site and soil conditions are unaltered, that the facility, design wastewater flow, and wastewater
21 characteristics are not increased, and that a wastewater system can be installed that meets the
22 permitting requirements in effect on the date the Improvement Permit was issued. Improvement
23 permits for which a plat or site plan is provided shall be valid without expiration. Improvement
24 permits for which a site plan is provided shall be valid for five years. The period of time for
25 which the permit is valid and a A statement that the permit an Improvement Permit or a
