27 applicable, or the intended use changes revocation or amendment if the intended use, design daily
28 flow, or site conditions change shall be displayed prominently on both the application form for
29 the permit and the permit.
30 …."
31 SECTION 3.(b) G.S. 130A-336 reads as rewritten:
32 "§ 130A-336. Improvement permit and construction authorization required.
33 (a) Any proposed site for a residence, place of business, or place of public assembly in
34 an area not served by an approved wastewater system shall be evaluated by either (i) the local
35 health department in accordance with rules adopted pursuant to this Article or (ii) by a
36 professional engineer, licensed soil scientist, or licensed geologist acting within the engineer's,
37 soil scientist's, or geologist's scope of work, as applicable, and pursuant to the conditions of the
38 engineered option permit in G.S. 130A-336.1 or the Authorized On-Site Wastewater Evaluator
39 permit option in G.S. 130A-336.2. An improvement permit issued by a local health department
40 shall include:
41 (1) For permits that are valid without expiration, a plat, or, for permits that are
42 valid for five years, A plat or a site plan.
43 (2) A description of the facility the proposed site is to serve.
44 (3) The proposed wastewater system and its location.
45 (4) The design wastewater flow and characteristics.
46 (5) The conditions for any site modifications.
47 (6) Any other information required by the rules of the Commission.
48 Neither the improvement permit nor the construction authorization shall be affected by change
49 of ownership of the site for the wastewater system provided both the site for the wastewater
50 system and the facility the system serves are unchanged and remain under the ownership or
51 control of the person owning the facility. No person shall commence or assist in the construction,
