1 location, or relocation of a residence, place of business, or place of public assembly in an area
2 not served by an approved wastewater system unless an improvement permit and a construction
3 authorization are obtained from the local health department unless that person is acting in
4 accordance with the conditions and criteria of an engineered option permit pursuant to
5 G.S. 130A-336.1 or the Authorized On-Site Wastewater Evaluator permit option pursuant to
6 G.S. 130A-336.2. This requirement shall not apply to a manufactured residence exhibited for sale
7 or stored for later sale and intended to be located at another site after sale.
8 (b) The local health department shall issue a construction authorization authorizing work
9 to proceed and the installation or repair of a wastewater system when it has determined after a
10 field investigation that the system can be installed and operated in compliance with this Article
11 and rules adopted pursuant to this Article. This construction authorization shall be valid for a
12 period equal to the period of validity of the improvement permit and may be issued at the same
13 time the improvement permit is issued. No person shall commence or assist in the installation,
14 construction, or repair of a wastewater system unless an improvement permit and a construction
15 authorization have been obtained from the Department or the local health department unless that
16 person is acting in accordance with the conditions and criteria of an engineered option permit
17 pursuant to G.S. 130A-336.1 or the Authorized On-Site Wastewater Evaluator permit option
18 pursuant to G.S. 130A-336.2. No improvement permit or construction authorization shall be
19 required for maintenance of a wastewater system. The Department and the local health
20 department may impose conditions on the issuance of an improvement permit and a construction
21 authorization. The Department or the local health department may delay the start of construction
22 of any system until a verification shows that site conditions are unchanged from the issuance of
23 the improvement permit, except that the verification shall not include a geological soil
24 assessment. The owner of the proposed wastewater system may accept or decline the findings of
25 a reassessment of the soils on the site.
26 …."
27 SECTION 3.(c) G.S. 130A-337 reads as rewritten:
28 "§ 130A-337. Inspection; operation permit required.
29 (a) No system of wastewater collection, treatment and disposal shall be covered or placed
30 into use by any person until an inspection by the local health department has determined that the
31 system has been installed or repaired in accordance with any conditions of the Improvement
32 Permit, the rules, and this Article.
33 (a1) Notwithstanding subsection (a) of this section, an applicant may contract with an
34 Authorized On-Site Wastewater Evaluator certified pursuant to Article 5 of Chapter 90A of the
35 General Statutes or an engineer licensed pursuant to Chapter 89C of the General Statutes to
36 conduct any required verifications or inspections. The evaluator or engineer shall provide the
37 applicant with written verification that all conditions of the Improvement Permit and
38 Construction Authorization have been met, including an as-built drawing meeting the standards
39 and scale of the local health department issuing the Construction Authorization as certified by
40 the evaluator. evaluator or engineer. The applicant may cover the system and place it into
41 operation upon receipt of the evaluator's written verification and shall submit the verification to
42 the local health department within two business days of receipt of the verification. The
43 Department, the Department's authorized agents, and the local health department shall be
44 discharged and released from any liabilities, duties, and responsibilities imposed by statute or
45 common law from any claim arising out of or attributed to the on-site wastewater system
46 installation.
47 …
48 (b) Upon determining that the system is properly installed or repaired and that the system
49 is capable of being operated in installation or repair of a wastewater system in accordance with
50 the conditions of the Improvement Permit, the rules, this Article and any conditions to be imposed
51 in the operation permit, Permit and the Construction Authorization, including any site
